        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 29 at 2:28PM MDT until August 29 at 3:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 228 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles southwest
of Springer, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Springer.

This includes Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 401 and 415.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
